######################################################################################

1. Time analysis 4bit (in ns)

4 bit CLA
    worst delay carry out - 5.973
    worst delay sum - 5.904

4 bit RCA
    worst delay carry out - 8.004
    worst delay sum - 7.608

######################################################################################

2. Time analysis 16bit (in ns)

16 bit CLA with ripple carry
    worst delay carry out - 9.825
    worst delay sum - 9.563

16 bit CLA with lookahead carry
    worst delay carry out - 7.363
    worst delay sum - 8.264

16 bit RCA
    worst delay carry out - 17.541
    worst delay sum - 16.780

    1. It can be observed that a CLA is significantly (almost 2x) faster than a RCA
    2. Also a CLA with an additional lookahead carry unit performs better than 
       simply rippling the carry

